[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm looking at the "chat observation" error logging, which currently supports all contexts, but only the ChatModel and plain are covered. It seems I should test if the ErrorLoggingObservationHandler can support configured AI observation contexts. That requires dependencies for embedding, image, chat client, and advisor classes; these might already be in transitive dependencies. I wonder if public constructors or builders are needed to construct contexts. It seems like I may need to dig deeper into the coverage stats too!
